lru-type.name: ML
lru-type.description: One laser is considered as the reference laser or the Master Laser while the second one, the Slave Laser (aka CTNLL), is being phase-locked to the reference laser in a subsystem called the Laser Synthesizer. Both Master Laser and Slave Laser signals are split in multiple outputs for amplification and distribution from the central building to the antennas via a fibre optic network reaching a distance up to 15 km.

baci-property.description: Returns the System Monitoring sticky error word. This function can be used to monitor the PML errors and offers quick insight about current and past error conditions on the various subsystems. Errors are determined by the checking the System Monitoring status word against different conditions depending on the system state. Once an error is flagged, it stays flagged until explicitly cleared by writing a 1 to the same bit position at the associated control point.

baci-property.description: Returns the laser monitoring alarm word. This function can be used to monitor the fibre laser alarms and offers quick insight about current alarms conditions affecting the fibre laser module. The fibre laser module embedded firmware checks every internal ADC signal against pre-defined limit values. In the event a value is out of the allowed range, an alarm condition is set at the corresponding position.
